Read: - Government Decision, Other Backward Bahujan Welfare Department, No. Ranio-2024 / Q. No.2 / VIJABHAJ-1, dated 27th September, 2024

Government Decisions: - Government Decisions for teachers and non-teaching staff appointed on or after 1st November, 2005 in Government Aided Primary / Secondary / Higher Secondary Ashramshalas, Vidyaniketans and Ashramshalas / Residential Schools for children of Sugarcane Harvesters belonging to Denotified Castes, Nomadic Tribes, Other Backward Classes and Special Backward Classes covered by the State Defined Contribution Pension Scheme (DCPS) under the control of Department of Other Backward Classes (OBC), Reference No. 1, D. The National Pension System (NPS) has been implemented under 27.09.2024.

Under the said system, the Government is approving the opening of new headings of accounts as follows to transfer the amount deposited in the Defined Contribution Pension Scheme (DCPS) accounts by the teaching and non-teaching staff of Visa-Aided Residential Ashramshalas.
